<br>
Then there seems to be a castle or a structure similar to it that has named mobs in it and everything is blue to my level 56 wizard.  Now I have no idea of Instrument of Nife will stack with these alternate exp or not, but at the camps my 53 pally used it on her weapon.  Imagine my surprise that a level 30 spell hits for 243 damage.  At level 53 we don't even have a spell that will hit undead for that much.  It does not however stack with divine might.  <br>
<br>
I found this of some interest.  I am not all that great with the mathematics as the rest of you are here <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   However I was impressed that a level 30 spell would do that sort of damage and I sure liked it.  It also seemed to proc a LOT.<br>
<br>
That is a nice zone on Bertox and as yet is not horribly overcrowded... yet <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Alyssandra Blackthorne, 56 Wizard<BR>
