</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaelodyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aelodyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/27/01 8:56:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13606.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/roevernon/images/Aeltn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Slay Undead 2 = hit harder, not more often</span><hr size=1> The vampires in Tenebrous are pretty tough individually; I doubt they are worth soloing. My pal is a 60 cleric and she goes pretty much oom nuking down one coterie centurion. I hunt there often, usually with the 60 cleric and a 55 mage. With the 3 of us we can kill any mob in the castle individually np, and do okay verses 2 or 3 at a time. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Instrument of Nife is your friend here</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. <br>
<br>
At the Tenebrous castle where we like to hunt, there are three kinds of vampyres: centurions, generals, and named. Centurions are blue/light blue at 54, generals and named are blue. The named are always winged: one is a warrior, one is a wizard, and one is an enchanter. All three named have around 25k hit points, hit for around 140, and, as usual, lifetap for 200 (all vampyres in tenebrous lifetap for 200). The wizard nukes for up to 600, and the enchanter will slow you. Malo + chain stun is your friend, all the named are extremely resistant. In addition to what lives in the castle, there are three vampyres from a nearby camp that will turn into wolves (one black + 2 grey) and walk a path from the camp into the castle, where they will linger in human form, and then back. They have a large agro radius, con blue at 54, and are impossible to root. Being vampyres, they lifetap for 200 and cast spells, even in wolf form. Be aware of the wandering zone trash as well, dire sonic bats and dire bats, for they will turn a victory into a loss very quickly if you are lom.<br>
<br>
LOOT: Coterie armor is common and crap, but good for twinking an extremely low level monk or beastlord. Coterie General armor (boots and cloaks only) is decent for mid to 50, and higher if you don't have better. The boots, in particular, rival iksar-hide boots for monks. The named commonly drop a nice gem, and very, very rarely drop some great items for warriors, SKs, and casters. I have yet to see anything useful to a paladin drop here. <p><b>Aelodyn Autumnflame<br>Sword of Tunare<br>The Nameless</b></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=13606.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessageRange?topicID=13606.topic&start=41&stop=46>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13662.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13647.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13606.topic&index=40><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=13606.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=13606.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=13606.topic>Subscribe</a> Cli